            "ignore": false,
            "order": 7,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": "  While both definitions  $P^{(A)}_{(t,T]}(\\chi)$  and  $\\tilde{P}^{(A)}_{(t,T]}(\\chi)$  appear to be reasonable, we prefer (2). We notice that this is different to the practice of using the column “Result curr. global” in the front office system SOPHIS for FX-hedged performance monitoring, because the latter essentially corresponds to the expression  $\\chi_T (A_T - A_t)$ .",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
